<p>If you wanted to <em>hide</em> the fact that the username was wrong, you can throw
a <code>BadCredentialsException</code> instead - you'll see me do that in a second.</p>
<p>Checking the password is <em>easy</em>: <code>$isValid = $this-&gt;get('security.password_encoder')</code>
<code>-&gt;isPasswordValid()</code>. Pass it the <code>$user</code> object and the raw HTTP Basic password
string: <code>$request-&gt;getPassword()</code>:</p>
